# Autonomous Research Agent

Autonomous research pipeline that accepts a topic and produces a structured report with citations.

This repository currently implements Phases P0-P10:

- P0: Discovery and technical design artifacts
- P1: Python project bootstrap and environment setup
- P2: LLM provider abstraction with OpenAI-first implementation and Anthropic compatibility stub
- P3: Planner prompt/schema, heuristics/caps, and persisted plan artifacts
- P4: Tavily search wrapper, URL dedupe/ranking, and candidate artifact persistence
- P5: Async fetch, HTML extraction/chunking, summarization, and relevance filtering
- P6: Notion persistence with idempotency, retry handling, and dead-letter artifacts
- P7: Citation-aware report composition with markdown and HTML rendering
- P8: Gmail delivery with token refresh, retry handling, and idempotent send keys
- P9: Unified CLI/API/web trigger interface with run status tracking
- P10: Runtime guardrails, run tracing artifacts, and failure alert hooks

## Quick Start

1. Create and activate a Python 3.11+ environment.
2. Install dependencies.

```bash
pip install -e .[dev]
```

3. Copy the environment template and provide secrets.

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

4. Start the API.

```bash
python -m app.main
```

The API serves:

- `GET /health`
- `POST /v1/research` (P9 unified run trigger)
- `GET /v1/research/runs/{run_id}` (P9 run status)
- `GET /v1/research/form` (P9 minimal web form)
- `POST /v1/research/plan` (P2-ready planner flow using the unified LLM interface)
- `POST /v1/research/candidates` (P4 plan + candidate URL collection)
- `POST /v1/research/findings` (P5 adds fetch/extract/summarize + filtered findings)
- `POST /v1/research/persist-findings` (P6 writes findings to Notion + dead-letter logging)
- `POST /v1/research/report` (P7 composes citation-grounded report markdown + HTML)
- `POST /v1/research/deliver` (P8 sends report via Gmail and records delivery artifacts)

P10 runtime controls and observability additions:

- Hard guardrails for request size, source/query caps, and run token budget
- Per-run trace artifact at `run_artifacts/<run_id>/run_trace.json`
- Trace/alert log streams at `logs/run_traces.jsonl` and `logs/alerts.jsonl`
- Repeated-failure and delivery-failure alert hooks (optional Slack emission)

## CLI Full-Run Command

```bash
python -m app.cli --query "State of enterprise RAG adoption" --email "analyst@company.com" --depth standard
```

## Phase Deliverables

- P0 docs: `docs/p0/`
- P1 bootstrap: `pyproject.toml`, `.env.example`, `app/settings.py`, app scaffold
- P2 abstraction: `app/providers/llm/` and planner/report modules
- P3 planner: `app/modules/planner/`, `app/utils/artifacts.py`, `docs/p3/`
- P4 search: `app/providers/mcp/tavily_search.py`, `app/modules/search/`, `docs/p4/`
- P5 processing: `app/modules/fetcher/`, `app/modules/summarizer/`, `docs/p5/`
- P6 persistence: `app/providers/mcp/notion.py`, `app/modules/notion/`, `docs/p6/`
- P7 reporting: `app/modules/reporting/`, `app/schemas/report.py`, `docs/p7/`
- P8 delivery: `app/providers/mcp/gmail.py`, `app/modules/delivery/`, `docs/p8/`
- P9 interfaces: `app/core/run_service.py`, `app/core/run_store.py`, `docs/p9/`
- P10 guardrails and observability: `app/core/guardrails.py`, `app/core/tracing.py`, `app/core/alerts.py`, `docs/p10/`
